thread.title: 'This Is Us' produces tears, ratings

author: Hal Boedeker
title: 'This Is Us' produces tears, ratings
text:
'This Is Us' produces tears, ratings This Is Us Ron Batzdorff/NBC Ron Cephas Jones as William, left, and Sterling K. Brown as Randall in 'This Is Us.' Ron Cephas Jones as William, left, and Sterling K. Brown as Randall in 'This Is Us.' (Ron Batzdorff/NBC) Hal Boedeker with 3.7 million, Fox with 2.6 million and The CW with 2.2 million. But thanks to “This Is Us,” NBC was tops with young adults.
ABC’s best was “The Middle” with 6.3 million fans. Fox’s best was soon-to-end “Bones” with 2.9 million. “The Flash” pulled in 2.7 million for The CW. 
In Orlando, Mark Harmon was again the overwhelming favorite with 273,298 total viewers, according to Nielsen ratings supplied to the Sentinel. The drama was followed by “Bull” with 175,084, “NCIS: New Orleans” with 172,663, “This Is Us” with 135,042 and Fox News’ “The O’Reilly Factor” with 117,861. 
With the local 18-to-49 age group, OWN’s “The Have and the Have Nots” ranked first, and “This Is Us” was second. They were followed by “NCIS,” “NCIS: New Orleans” and “Bull.”
